Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The operator's terminal `⊑`-introduction rule, or `none` when it saturates to another operator's\nterminal. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.terminal?","kind":"def","line":49,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.terminal?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.lean#L49-L49"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.rewrites\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">VCGen</span>.<span class=\"name\">LatticeOp</span>.<span class=\"name\">rewrites</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp\">LatticeOp</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Distribution and unfolding equalities that saturate the operator applied to state arguments. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.rewrites","kind":"def","line":46,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.rewrites","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.lean#L46-L46"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.numConst\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">VCGen</span>.<span class=\"name\">LatticeOp</span>.<span class=\"name\">numConst</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp\">LatticeOp</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The number of leading arguments held constant during rule construction: the operator's carrier\ntype and its typeclass instances. The operands and excess state arguments after them become the\nrule's schematic parameters. `2` for a connective over a `CompleteLattice` carrier; `0` for a\nmonomorphic operator. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.numConst","kind":"def","line":44,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.numConst","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.lean#L44-L44"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.head\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">VCGen</span>.<span class=\"name\">LatticeOp</span>.<span class=\"name\">head</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp\">LatticeOp</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Head constant of the operator this split decomposes. Keys the `latticeOps` table. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.head","kind":"def","line":39,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.head","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.lean#L39-L39"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">VCGen</span>.<span class=\"name\">LatticeOp</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lean.Name</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lean.Name</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lean.Name</a></span> → <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp\">Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp</a></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.mk","kind":"ctor","line":33,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.lean#L33-L49"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">VCGen</span>.<span class=\"name\">LatticeOp</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"How to decompose a lattice operator `head … s⃗` on the RHS of an entailment: the distribution and\nunfolding `rewrites` that saturate it, and the terminal `⊑`-introduction `terminals` that close the\nreduced form. `head` keys the split in the `latticeOps` table. A built-in connective contributes an\nempty split (the shared built-in rewrites and terminals cover it); a frame operator adds its own. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp","kind":"structure","line":33,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.LatticeOp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.lean#L33-L49"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.FrameInferenceProc\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">VCGen</span>.<span class=\"name\">FrameInferenceProc</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A frame inference procedure: given the resource type `R` of the applicable frame operator\n`op : R → Pred → Pred`, the goal's precondition, the `wp` metadata of a spec-ready program, and the\nspec's precondition instantiated at the call site (the RHS of the spec's precondition VC `pre ⊑ ·`),\noptionally produce a frame `F : R` to peel off. `none` leaves the spec to apply directly.\n\nThe caller instantiates and hash-conses `F` before the speculative spec application's metavariable\ncontext is reset, so `F` may mention metavariables assigned during that application. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.FrameInferenceProc","kind":"def","line":23,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.FrameInferenceProc","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/FrameProc.lean#L23-L31"}}],"imports":["Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.WPApp","Lean.Meta.AppBuilder","Std.Internal.Do.Order.Basic"],"instances":[{"className":"Inhabited","name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.instInhabitedFrameProcs","typeNames":["Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.FrameProcs"]}],"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.FrameProc"}